JOHANNESBURG - South Africa Under-20 lost to Italy 2-0 in their FIFA Under-20 World Cup Group D clash at the Suwon World Cup Stadium, in Korea Republic on Wednesday.South Africa were outclassed for much of the encounter, and fashioned little in the way of genuine chances on the Italian goal until the African side had gone two goals down.READ: We are disappointed - SA Under-20 coach SenongIt was the second loss in a row for the South Africans who lost 2-1 to Japan in their opening game of the competition on Sunday.South Africa, after two games, occupy bottom spot in the group without any points and a goal difference on minus-three. Italy, Japan and Uruguay all have three points.African News Agency